Heat oven to 400 degrees F. Beat egg and water in small bowl with fork. Unfold pastry sheet on lightly floured surface. Roll pastry sheet into 14-inch square. Spread preserves on pastry to within 2 inches of edge. Sprinkle with cranberries and almonds. Place cheese in center of pastry. Fold pastry up over cheese to cover. Trim excess pastry and press to seal. Brush seam with egg mixture. Please seam-side down onto baking sheet. Brush with egg mixture. Bake 20 minutes or until pastry is golden brown. Let stand 45 minutes. Serve with crackers.